data.description: DISCLOSURE: I am a licensed real estate salesperson.  Welcome to your dream home in a serene, walkable community just 8 minutes from downtown Greenville. Nestled just off I-385, this charming townhome offers the perfect blend of quiet community and convenience. A grocery store and series of restaurants are all within a 2 minute drive.  All lawn maintenance, water, trash, pest control, and exterior maintenance is handled by the HOA. You'll love the brand new flooring throughout and the fresh paint on all cabinets and walls.  Upstairs, you'll find two generously sized bedrooms, each with its own private bathroom. The primary suite offers a spacious dual-sided closet and an en-suite bathroom. The second bedroom is perfect for a bedroom or as a home office.  Step outside onto your private patio and enjoy the tranquility of this quiet community. Surrounded by large, beautiful trees, it's the perfect spot for morning coffee or evening relaxation.  This community offers fantastic amenities, including a pool for those hot summer days and a clubhouse for your social gatherings.  With downtown Greenville just 8 minutes away, you'll have easy access to all the dining, shopping, and entertainment options the city has to offer. Plus, you're just minutes from I-385, making commuting a breeze.  Don't miss the opportunity to make this townhome your new sanctuary in Greenville. It's the perfect blend of convenience, comfort, and community. Schedule your showing today.
